## Evidence rule

Do not claim success without evidence.

If a command cannot be run, report:

- which command;
- why it could not run;
- what you ran instead;
- what risk remains.

## Stop conditions

Stop and report back if:

- the task requires product or architecture decisions not included in the packet;
- tests reveal broader existing failures unrelated to your changes;
- the requested change conflicts with current architecture;
- secrets, credentials, payments, auth, data deletion, or production config are involved without explicit authorization;
- you need to modify more than the approved scope.
